BLACK MESA ALIEN RESEARCH LAB, RESEARCH FACILITY


Sam, the tunnel has opened up into a large, high room. We can finally stand up straight, stop squinting in the darkness, and realize where we've ended up. We've ended up in the very heart of the local xenobiology research facility. A research facility. Three labs, three colors, three sets of problems. Orange, red, blue. Like a traffic light stuck in chaos mode.

They study aliens here. They don't just look at them through glass; they cut them up, dig into them, test their strength. Basically, they do all the things that would earn normal people a Nobel Prize, only to become the first casualty during an invasion. Now these labs are empty. The scientists have scattered, hidden, locked themselves in their offices, and are praying they won't be found by the very people they were studying.

But someone remains. And our task is not just to get through the complex, but to find the two surviving scientists and lead them to the blue exit. Because LAB3, the blue one, is our ticket to the surface. That's the emergency exit. That's where we can escape this hell.

Scientists aren't fools. They know the labs are dangerous. They've probably locked themselves in some utility room, server room, or break room. Perhaps one in the orange one, the other in the red one. Or both in the blue one, but they won't risk leaving without us. We'll have to search. And hope we find them before the creatures do.
